   {:e #blake3 "1e943cae3bfa8c72e2f8747e28c758be46c37537fa41b83ee91e3e1d2b22627d" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: The Universal Accumulator (UA-1) extends observe_datom with 4 new accumulator domains. The fundamental invariant is that incremental == batch for ALL domains. This test task proves that invariant algebraically.\n\nUNIT TESTS (8 tests):\n\n1. test_isp_incremental_equals_batch: Build store via apply_datoms (incremental). Build second store via from_datoms (batch, same datom set). Assert views.isp_intent_entities == live_projections intent entities, views.isp_spec_entities == live_projections spec entities, views.isp_impl_entities == live_projections impl entities. Also assert datom counts match. This is the ISP isomorphism proof.\n\n2. test_task_index_exact_counts: Create 10 tasks. Transition 3 to in_progress, 5 to closed. Assert views.task_counts_live() == (2, 3, 5). Then transition 2 in_progress to closed. Assert views.task_counts_live() == (2, 1, 7). Proves the decrement-old/increment-new dance works correctly.\n\n3. test_task_index_matches_all_tasks: Build store with 50 tasks in various states via random transitions. Assert views.task_counts_live() matches all_tasks(store) grouped by resolved live status. Uses the existing task infrastructure.\n\n4. test_telemetry_single_pass_equals_multi: Build store with sessions, spec elements, tasks with spec refs, and harvests. Assert views.telemetry() matches telemetry_from_store(store) for ALL fields: session count, spec count, tx count, harvest count, observation count.\n\n5. test_beta_1_union_find_equals_eigendecomposition: Build stores with known cycle structures: (a) acyclic chain A→B→C, beta_1=0. (b) single cycle A→B→C→A, beta_1=1. (c) two independent cycles, beta_1=2. (d) complex graph with 5 cycles. Assert views.beta_1() matches compute_beta_1(store) in ALL cases.\n\n6. test_beta_1_incremental_monotone: In an append-only store, beta_1 is monotonically non-decreasing (adding edges can only create cycles, never destroy them). Verify via proptest.\n\n7. test_universal_isomorphism_comprehensive: The MASTER test. Build store through a realistic 8-phase sequence (genesis, schema, 50 spec elements, 100 impl links, 200 observations with concepts, 50 tasks with status transitions, 10 harvests, 10 sessions). Build batch store from same datom set. Assert ALL accumulator domains match: fitness (existing), ISP entities, ISP counts, task index, telemetry, beta_1. This single test proves the entire homomorphism property.\n\n8. test_empty_store_all_views_zero: Fresh Store::genesis() has all accumulator values at zero/empty. Sanity check.\n\nPROPERTY-BASED TESTS (3 proptests):\n\n9. proptest_isp_monotone: For any store growth (add datoms), ISP entity set sizes are monotonically non-decreasing. Mirrors existing live_projections_entity_count_monotone_under_growth.\n\n10. proptest_task_counts_sum_invariant: views.task_open + views.task_in_progress + views.task_closed == number of distinct task entities. This is a counting invariant that must hold regardless of transition history.\n\n11. proptest_universal_isomorphism: For any sequence of 0-500 random datoms with realistic attribute distribution, fold(observe_datom) == batch compute for ALL domains.\n\nE2E SCRIPT: scripts/e2e_performance_guard.sh\n\nCHECK 1: braid status on real 105K datom store: wall-clock < 2s (3 runs, median)\nCHECK 2: braid observe: wall-clock < 1s (3 runs, median)\nCHECK 3: braid task list: wall-clock < 1s\nCHECK 4: braid seed --inject AGENTS.md: wall-clock < 3s (relaxed target pre-P5)\n\nLOGGING: Each check logs: (A) wall-clock time in ms, (B) store size (datoms/entities/txns), (C) which check, (D) PASS/FAIL with threshold. On failure, suggests which task to prioritize.\n\nFAILURE DIAGNOSTICS: For isomorphism tests, on mismatch: dump the full datom sequence, the running accumulator state at each step, and the batch-computed reference values. Diff the two to identify which datom caused divergence. For beta_1: dump the graph adjacency list and the Union-Find parent array.\n\nDEPENDS-ON: UA-1 (Universal Accumulator implementation)." :op :assert}
